    <text>
        <body>
            <msDesc>
                <msIdentifier>
                    <msName type="general">Tetraevangelion.</msName>
                    <country>Greece,</country>
                    <settlement>Athos, Mt.,</settlement>
                    <repository>Monastery of Zographou,</repository>
                    <idno type="shelfmark"> Zographou III.e.8, </idno>
                    <idno type="catalogue">219.</idno>
                    <note><listBibl>
                            <bibl><ref>Каталог 1994: 219; </ref><ref>Опис 1985: 32.</ref></bibl>
                        </listBibl></note>
                </msIdentifier>
                <physDesc>
                    <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="paper">
                            <support><material>Paper.</material></support>
                            <extent>325 ff.</extent>
                        </supportDesc>
                        <layoutDesc>
                            <layout writtenLines="22" columns="1">In 1 column, 22 lines per
                                page.</layout>
                        </layoutDesc>
                    </objectDesc>
                    <decoDesc>
                        <p>Four headpieces in Balkan style, interlaced initials with geometrical and
                            floral motifs.</p>
                    </decoDesc>
                </physDesc>
                <scribeDesc xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0">
                    <summary>The scribe were most probably the one who copied the 1451 Skopje
                        Menaion (Church Historical and Archival Institute, Sofia, 489) and part of
                        the 15th-c. Miscellany with services and vitae of St. John of
                        Rila.</summary>
                    <scribe>
                        <name>Anonymous.</name>
                        <scriptDesc script="cyrs">
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Semi-uncial.</p>
                        </scriptDesc>
                        <scribeLang>
                            <orthography>
                                <p>Bulgarian two-jer and two-jus orthography.</p>
                            </orthography>
                        </scribeLang>
                    </scribe>
                </scribeDesc>
                <msContents>
                    <summary>Contains the Titles and the Prefaces by Theophylaktos, archbishop of
                        Okhrid for each Gospel; the Synaxarion commemorates SS. Simeon and Sabbas of
                        Serbia. Contains also part of the Akathistos hymn in honour of the
                        Theotokos.</summary>
                </msContents>
                <history>
                    <origin><origDate>15th c., 3rd quarter.</origDate><note>The MS is copied by the
                            scribe who copied the so-called Skopie Menaion (Church Historical and
                            Archival Institute, Sofia, 489) and part of the Miscellany with works
                            for St. John of Rila from the 2nd half of the 15th c. (Rila Monastery,
                            1/26). <bibl><ref>Славянские рукописи Афонских обителей 1999: 81, №
                                    169.</ref></bibl></note></origin>
                </history>
            </msDesc>
